quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  26,137,"This is nothing\", they said, \"other than the customary manner of thinking of those of old used often enough that it bred the same habit in you"
  26,138,"Nor, as you think, shall We be subjected to a retributive punishment"
  26,139,"And they disbelieved him and refused credence to Our message wherefore We reduced them to a useless form. This is indeed emblematic of Allah's Omnipotence and Authority, but most of them denied Allah Who brought them into existence"
  26,140,"And Allah, your Creator, is indeed AL-Aziz and AL-Rahim"
  26,141,And just as averse were the people of Thamud (the Thamudites) who refused to accept Allah's message and Messengers
  26,142,"Their brother Saleh said to them: \"Will you not listen to exhortation and keep in awe of Allah, your Creator, and entertain the profound reverence dutiful to Him"
  26,143,"I am\", he added, a Messenger entrusted with a divine message and here do I relate it to you in honour and sincerity"
  26,144,A message exacting your reverence for Allah and obedience to me
  26,145,"I do not charge you a price for imparting to you Allah's disclosures of divine knowledge, wisdom and practical divinity. My reward rests in His hands, Creator of the worlds"
  26,146,"Do you think\", he said, \"you will be left to form imaginary visions of unrealities expecting to enjoy the grace of Allah which abounds in you without being tried"
  26,147,"You live in splendour, you hold in possession orchards and flowing springs"
  26,148,And vegetal growth and-date palms whose enclosed spadix carries tender delicious and easily digestible fruits
  26,149,And you skillfully carve the mountains into homes wherein you make abode
  26,150,A divine grace which exacting your reverence for Allah and obedience to me
  26,151,And I advise you not to comply with the command of those who are extravagant in their accounts of themselves nor yield to their irreverent principles and authority
  26,152,They create discord on earth and mischief is natural to them and never do they attempt reform or change for the better
  26,153,"Yet the response of his people was pitifully unfavourable. They said to him: \"You are one of those influenced by witchcraft and therefore bewitched"
  26,154,"You are only a mortal like us,\" they said, \"wherefore you could not be singled out for the prerogative of prophethood, and if you are indeed declaring the truth then present us with a divine sign convincing our minds and proving the conclusion"
  26,155,"This\", he said, \"is a she-camel which is entitled to a share of the drinking water just as you are entitled to a share. She is to have her share on a certain day and you have yours on an alternate day"
  26,156,"And\", he added, \"you are warned not to harm her lest you suffer the torment laid upon the damned on a momentous Day"
  26,157,Nevertheless they defiantly disabled her by cutting her hamstring muscles. (Their outrage on consecrated objects invited their ruin) which led to pining regrets and vain repentances
  26,158,They were overtaken by Allah's wrath which spoke thunder. This is indeed emblematic of His Omnipotence and Authority but most of them denied Him Who brought them into existence
  26,159,"Allah, your Creator, is indeed AL-Aziz and AL-Rahim"